1
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:29,719
=Soft-Hearted God=

2
00:00:29,720 --> 00:00:32,999
=Episode 18=
(I look at stars from the abyss.)

3
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:37,295
(I will rescue myself and conquer all.)

4
00:00:53,940 --> 00:00:55,980
Xi!

5
00:00:57,575 --> 00:00:59,895
(Explosives)

6
00:01:00,420 --> 00:01:01,900
Xi!

7
00:01:02,580 --> 00:01:03,660
Zhao?

8
00:01:04,620 --> 00:01:05,940
Is that you?

9
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:12,740
Zhao.

10
00:01:48,300 --> 00:01:50,100
What are you doing?

11
00:01:50,780 --> 00:01:53,139
Don't you know you're hurt?

12
00:01:53,140 --> 00:01:54,579
You're no longer a god.

13
00:01:54,580 --> 00:01:55,979
Mortals are fragile.

14
00:01:55,980 --> 00:01:58,100
You're going to die like this.

15
00:02:09,660 --> 00:02:11,020
I thought...

16
00:02:12,780 --> 00:02:14,740
I thought I had lost you.

17
00:02:16,660 --> 00:02:19,460
I'm here. I'm right here.

18
00:02:19,980 --> 00:02:21,620
Don't cry, please.

19
00:02:29,420 --> 00:02:30,820
It's fine now.

20
00:02:41,580 --> 00:02:43,939
Zhao, be careful. Your wound might tear.

21
00:02:43,940 --> 00:02:45,419
Kicking him was letting him off easy.

22
00:02:45,420 --> 00:02:46,980
I should have thrown him into the fire.

23
00:02:47,180 --> 00:02:49,099
Chief Zhang was only
thinking of the village.

24
00:02:49,100 --> 00:02:51,099
He was afraid
of spreading this strange plant.

25
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:52,140
But he didn't know

26
00:02:52,220 --> 00:02:53,820
that the whole village

27
00:02:54,220 --> 00:02:55,660
was already infected.

28
00:02:57,380 --> 00:02:59,100
The others were infected too?

29
00:02:59,180 --> 00:03:01,220
Chief Zhang, are you okay?

30
00:03:01,620 --> 00:03:02,899
Xi, are you okay?

31
00:03:02,900 --> 00:03:04,100
Are you hurt?

32
00:03:06,060 --> 00:03:07,179
Ouch, it hurts.

33
00:03:07,180 --> 00:03:09,980
Touch my wife again,
and I'll make you regret it.

34
00:03:12,660 --> 00:03:14,459
What do you mean, "your wife"?

35
00:03:14,460 --> 00:03:15,219
You...

36
00:03:15,220 --> 00:03:16,540
Enough, Chief Zhang.

37
00:03:16,660 --> 00:03:17,700
Now,

38
00:03:17,820 --> 00:03:19,540
so many people
have this strange illness.

39
00:03:19,660 --> 00:03:21,780
I need some time to research.

40
00:03:22,020 --> 00:03:23,220
During this period,

41
00:03:23,460 --> 00:03:24,899
could you help me

42
00:03:24,900 --> 00:03:26,700
calm the villagers in the hall?

43
00:03:26,820 --> 00:03:28,339
This is my duty.

44
00:03:28,340 --> 00:03:29,660
I'm obliged to do it.

45
00:03:30,780 --> 00:03:32,060
Let's go.

46
00:03:32,180 --> 00:03:33,220
What are you doing?

47
00:03:33,820 --> 00:03:36,060
You're awake and still want to lie down?

48
00:03:36,100 --> 00:03:37,219
Get up and walk.

49
00:03:37,220 --> 00:03:37,939
Honey, let's go.

50
00:03:37,940 --> 00:03:38,940
Wait.

51
00:03:40,060 --> 00:03:41,459
I'm injured.

52
00:03:41,460 --> 00:03:42,179
You two...

53
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:42,779
Xi.

54
00:03:42,780 --> 00:03:44,500
Don't touch her.

55
00:03:47,020 --> 00:03:47,820
Here.

56
00:03:49,660 --> 00:03:50,780
Thank you.

57
00:03:52,220 --> 00:03:52,939
For you.

58
00:03:52,940 --> 00:03:54,540
Chief Zhang and Lady He?

59
00:03:54,620 --> 00:03:55,820
They've returned.

60
00:03:56,060 --> 00:03:56,819
Chief Zhang.

61
00:03:56,820 --> 00:03:57,779
My lady,

62
00:03:57,780 --> 00:03:59,499
you've finally returned.

63
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:00,659
Everyone, look.

64
00:04:00,660 --> 00:04:01,779
Chief Zhang's neck.

65
00:04:01,780 --> 00:04:03,420
He's also infected.

66
00:04:05,060 --> 00:04:06,420
He's infected too.

67
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:10,380
Lady He, have you found a cure?

68
00:04:10,740 --> 00:04:14,099
My heart is in my mouth.

69
00:04:14,100 --> 00:04:15,739
Will we die?

70
00:04:15,740 --> 00:04:17,179
Chief Zhang, Lady He,

71
00:04:17,180 --> 00:04:18,259
please let me return home.

72
00:04:18,260 --> 00:04:20,539
I have a wife and children to care for.

73
00:04:20,540 --> 00:04:21,379
Yes.

74
00:04:21,380 --> 00:04:23,059
I must go back as well.

75
00:04:23,060 --> 00:04:24,380
Everyone, don't worry.

76
00:04:24,540 --> 00:04:26,499
I've made some progress.

77
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:28,619
I'll send out some medicinal soup soon.

78
00:04:28,620 --> 00:04:29,779
It may not cure the illness,

79
00:04:29,780 --> 00:04:31,339
but it should help control the symptoms.

80
00:04:31,340 --> 00:04:32,339
Thank you, Lady He.

81
00:04:32,340 --> 00:04:33,700
We trust you, Lady He.

82
00:04:40,380 --> 00:04:44,380
The vile plant thrives
by parasitic attachment.

83
00:04:44,820 --> 00:04:46,580
It feeds on blood.

84
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:48,420
I shall name it the Verdant Decay.

85
00:04:49,220 --> 00:04:51,420
The medicinal soup you gave out

86
00:04:51,540 --> 00:04:53,700
is meant to reassure the people,
isn't it?

87
00:04:56,220 --> 00:04:57,820
Throughout history,
when epidemics spread,

88
00:04:57,900 --> 00:04:59,580
fear spreads faster.

89
00:05:00,460 --> 00:05:02,020
Only by calming them

90
00:05:03,020 --> 00:05:04,660
can we treat the disease properly.

91
00:05:09,020 --> 00:05:12,220
How about we go through
these ancient texts together?

92
00:05:12,900 --> 00:05:15,220
Perhaps there's
a similar condition recorded.

93
00:05:15,780 --> 00:05:17,460
That's just what I had in mind.
Come sit.

94
00:05:35,580 --> 00:05:36,339
Nice!

95
00:05:36,340 --> 00:05:40,020
The hero killed the giant bug
with a punch.

96
00:05:42,580 --> 00:05:43,780
What's wrong?

97
00:05:45,140 --> 00:05:46,339
Hey.

98
00:05:46,340 --> 00:05:47,139
Wake up.

99
00:05:47,140 --> 00:05:48,460
Is he dead?

100
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:49,699
He's dead.

101
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:50,819
This disease kills people.

102
00:05:50,820 --> 00:05:52,019
Are we all going to die too?

103
00:05:52,020 --> 00:05:53,580
Get Lady He here!

104
00:06:07,780 --> 00:06:08,900
Xi,

105
00:06:09,260 --> 00:06:11,020
more and more people are dying.

106
00:06:11,380 --> 00:06:13,100
The panic is growing.

107
00:06:13,900 --> 00:06:15,580
You must hurry.

108
00:06:27,660 --> 00:06:29,736
It's been over a month now,

109
00:06:29,737 --> 00:06:31,830
and there no signs of improvement.

110
00:06:32,020 --> 00:06:34,540
More and more people are dying.

111
00:06:39,060 --> 00:06:41,659
Can Lady He even cure us?

112
00:06:41,660 --> 00:06:42,579
If not,

113
00:06:42,580 --> 00:06:44,019
we should return home.

114
00:06:44,020 --> 00:06:46,020
It's better than dying here.

115
00:06:46,900 --> 00:06:48,780
I can't take it anymore.

116
00:06:50,140 --> 00:06:52,020
We're going to die anyway.

117
00:06:52,780 --> 00:06:53,980
Why not just pull it out?

118
00:06:54,020 --> 00:06:54,900
Maybe...

119
00:06:55,140 --> 00:06:56,780
Maybe there'll be a glimmer of hope.

120
00:07:05,460 --> 00:07:07,700
Stop! You'll kill yourself!

121
00:07:17,060 --> 00:07:18,939
Rather than waiting for death here,

122
00:07:18,940 --> 00:07:20,699
it would be better to die together

123
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:21,899
with my wife and children.

124
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:23,459
They are lying to us.

125
00:07:23,460 --> 00:07:25,139
- I want to go home.
- We want to go home.

126
00:07:25,140 --> 00:07:26,259
I want to go home.

127
00:07:26,260 --> 00:07:27,139
Me too.

128
00:07:27,140 --> 00:07:28,580
Let us go home.

129
00:07:29,380 --> 00:07:30,699
Please, don't go out yet.

130
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:32,579
It will spread the disease faster.

131
00:07:32,580 --> 00:07:35,139
Then, your entire family
will be infected.

132
00:07:35,140 --> 00:07:36,379
We want to go home!

133
00:07:36,380 --> 00:07:38,140
Please believe me.

134
00:07:38,700 --> 00:07:40,379
We want to go home.

135
00:07:40,380 --> 00:07:41,259
Let us go home.

136
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:42,260
Everyone.

137
00:07:50,260 --> 00:07:52,820
Anyone who dares lay a finger on Xi

138
00:07:53,820 --> 00:07:56,020
should first answer to my sword.

139
00:07:56,820 --> 00:07:58,219
Her lady has worked day and night

140
00:07:58,220 --> 00:07:59,019
to save you all.

141
00:07:59,020 --> 00:08:00,139
She hasn't slept.

142
00:08:00,140 --> 00:08:01,700
She's exhausted.

143
00:08:01,780 --> 00:08:04,580
Yet, all you do is complain.

144
00:08:04,900 --> 00:08:05,780
My lady,

145
00:08:06,340 --> 00:08:07,699
they are so ungrateful.

146
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:09,100
Why bother with them?

147
00:08:10,340 --> 00:08:11,699
Let's just leave them.

148
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:13,220
Let them perish on their own.

149
00:08:15,220 --> 00:08:16,780
As a healer,

150
00:08:17,340 --> 00:08:19,220
this is my duty.

151
00:08:19,780 --> 00:08:20,780
Everyone,

152
00:08:21,380 --> 00:08:22,700
I have a method.

153
00:08:23,020 --> 00:08:24,580
Who is willing to help me?

154
00:08:25,260 --> 00:08:26,459
Tell us about it.

155
00:08:26,460 --> 00:08:27,379
Tell us.

156
00:08:27,380 --> 00:08:29,020
Cut out the infected part.

157
00:08:30,020 --> 00:08:31,900
Remove all the vile roots

158
00:08:32,340 --> 00:08:33,579
from the flesh and blood.

159
00:08:33,580 --> 00:08:34,579
If it fails,

160
00:08:34,580 --> 00:08:36,660
we'll just lose a leg.

161
00:08:36,900 --> 00:08:38,740
This isn't a good method.

162
00:08:40,820 --> 00:08:42,819
Who would dare do that?

163
00:08:42,820 --> 00:08:43,939
Exactly.

164
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:44,700
Yeah.

165
00:08:44,820 --> 00:08:45,899
Exactly.

166
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:47,019
Will that work?

167
00:08:47,020 --> 00:08:48,100
I'll do it.

168
00:08:49,780 --> 00:08:51,259
Hua, don't fool around.

169
00:08:51,260 --> 00:08:54,139
You're so young. How could you bear
the pain of the root-severing rite?

170
00:08:54,140 --> 00:08:56,140
My lady, I'm not afraid.

171
00:08:56,220 --> 00:08:58,499
You gave me this life.

172
00:08:58,500 --> 00:08:59,819
If it weren't for you,

173
00:08:59,820 --> 00:09:01,460
I would have been dead long ago.

174
00:09:02,020 --> 00:09:03,579
If I can save everyone,

175
00:09:03,580 --> 00:09:04,780
I'm willing to do it.

176
00:09:04,940 --> 00:09:06,700
My lady, I feel the same.

177
00:09:08,060 --> 00:09:09,580
Testing both seedling and flower

178
00:09:10,100 --> 00:09:11,700
beats testing only one.

179
00:09:36,260 --> 00:09:37,340
Alright.

180
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:39,180
This is a painkiller.

181
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:41,940
Once you drink it,
you will no longer feel pain.

182
00:09:42,860 --> 00:09:44,499
My lady, don't cry.

183
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:46,659
I still have many books left to read.

184
00:09:46,660 --> 00:09:48,060
I'll be fine.

185
00:09:48,780 --> 00:09:50,980
My lady, we believe in you.

186
00:09:56,740 --> 00:09:57,740
Okay.

187
00:09:58,180 --> 00:09:59,180
Here.

188
00:10:58,260 --> 00:10:59,220
Xi.

189
00:11:03,780 --> 00:11:06,420
I've removed all the roots.

190
00:11:07,020 --> 00:11:08,940
If they don't relapse by tomorrow,

191
00:11:09,660 --> 00:11:11,180
it's a success.

192
00:11:14,020 --> 00:11:15,340
I'm fine.

193
00:11:15,620 --> 00:11:17,340
I'm just a little tired.

194
00:11:26,140 --> 00:11:27,539
This is bad.

195
00:11:27,540 --> 00:11:30,740
He Xi has also contracted
the Verdant Decay.

196
00:11:34,140 --> 00:11:36,019
If we had gone to the capital
from the beginning,

197
00:11:36,020 --> 00:11:37,659
perhaps we would have been cured.

198
00:11:37,660 --> 00:11:38,620
Exactly.

199
00:11:39,380 --> 00:11:40,500
Let's go.

200
00:11:40,780 --> 00:11:42,580
Let's go.

201
00:12:08,380 --> 00:12:09,460
Everyone,

202
00:12:11,020 --> 00:12:13,820
we will know if Hua and Bai

203
00:12:14,380 --> 00:12:15,820
will recover

204
00:12:16,260 --> 00:12:17,980
by tomorrow.

205
00:12:18,100 --> 00:12:19,860
It's the coldest of winters right now.

206
00:12:20,540 --> 00:12:22,340
With your weakened bodies,

207
00:12:22,780 --> 00:12:24,820
going to the capital for treatment
is not feasible.

208
00:12:24,900 --> 00:12:28,100
You might not survive
after leaving the mountains.

209
00:12:28,420 --> 00:12:30,100
If any of you wish to leave,

210
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:32,580
we will not keep you.

211
00:12:36,380 --> 00:12:38,340
Staying here won't cure us either.

212
00:12:40,380 --> 00:12:41,980
Should we just wait for death here?

213
00:13:14,300 --> 00:13:15,820
Everyone, please calm down.

214
00:13:17,660 --> 00:13:19,940
It's just one more day to wait.

215
00:13:20,620 --> 00:13:22,220
We shall wait another day.

216
00:13:25,260 --> 00:13:26,659
Chief Zhang is right.

217
00:13:26,660 --> 00:13:27,779
Let's listen to him.

218
00:13:27,780 --> 00:13:28,419
Alright.

219
00:13:28,420 --> 00:13:29,499
Let's wait another day.

220
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:31,460
Let's wait.

221
00:13:43,140 --> 00:13:43,860
Zhao.

222
00:13:43,980 --> 00:13:44,860
Zhao!

223
00:13:49,180 --> 00:13:50,700
You didn't die?

224
00:13:51,420 --> 00:13:52,980
No matter how great

225
00:13:53,660 --> 00:13:56,220
your medical skills,

226
00:13:56,540 --> 00:13:58,979
do you think a mere mortal like you

227
00:13:58,980 --> 00:14:01,460
could survive without me
after having your heart removed?

228
00:14:01,900 --> 00:14:04,300
Then I shall remove it again

229
00:14:04,780 --> 00:14:06,860
until I have eliminated you completely.

230
00:14:08,380 --> 00:14:09,779
It's too late,

231
00:14:09,780 --> 00:14:11,779
my dear He Xi.

232
00:14:11,780 --> 00:14:15,100
If not for your heart incision
and opening of the gateways,

233
00:14:15,380 --> 00:14:18,180
I, with my meager powers,

234
00:14:18,620 --> 00:14:23,180
could never have gotten my hands
on this forbidden demon root technique.

235
00:14:23,260 --> 00:14:24,980
Unless the demon root is removed,

236
00:14:25,420 --> 00:14:26,979
the demon heart will not die.

237
00:14:26,980 --> 00:14:27,899
Do you know

238
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:30,259
how much pain I endured
the moment you threw me

239
00:14:30,260 --> 00:14:31,379
into the fire pit?

240
00:14:31,380 --> 00:14:33,180
You shouldn't have hurt Zhao.

241
00:14:33,980 --> 00:14:36,860
I hurt him? He wanted to kill me.

242
00:14:37,020 --> 00:14:38,500
I was just born.

243
00:14:38,860 --> 00:14:41,100
I didn't even have my own body yet.

244
00:14:41,260 --> 00:14:42,980
I had done nothing,

245
00:14:43,620 --> 00:14:45,820
yet Heavenly Dao decreed me a demon

246
00:14:46,140 --> 00:14:49,060
and sent Ye Zhao to chase and kill me.

247
00:14:49,260 --> 00:14:50,700
Heaven gave me life

248
00:14:50,740 --> 00:14:51,979
but did not let me live.

249
00:14:51,980 --> 00:14:53,460
What sense is there in this?

250
00:14:54,380 --> 00:14:56,340
Rather than waiting to die

251
00:14:57,540 --> 00:15:00,500
and be a mere pawn of Heavenly Dao,

252
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:03,139
it's better to be the one
holding the chess pieces

253
00:15:03,140 --> 00:15:04,499
and play you all to death.

254
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:07,139
Watch closely with your eyes wide open

255
00:15:07,140 --> 00:15:10,100
as I use the Red Spider Lily seeds

256
00:15:10,780 --> 00:15:15,100
to tear them all apart step by step.

257
00:15:16,780 --> 00:15:19,580
You caused the Verdant Decay?

258
00:15:19,860 --> 00:15:21,940
It was us.

259
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:23,980
I used your body

260
00:15:24,380 --> 00:15:27,899
to plant the Red Spider Lily seeds
inside them.

261
00:15:27,900 --> 00:15:29,299
I want the gods to taste

262
00:15:29,300 --> 00:15:31,580
the flavor of betrayal
by all living beings.

263
00:15:31,780 --> 00:15:33,259
The common people are innocent.

264
00:15:33,260 --> 00:15:34,499
Trampling on lives like this,

265
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:36,300
what do you really want?

266
00:15:37,620 --> 00:15:39,940
Since you're so eager to know,

267
00:15:40,660 --> 00:15:44,420
I will leave you with a pair of eyes.

268
00:15:44,740 --> 00:15:46,859
You can watch carefully

269
00:15:46,860 --> 00:15:49,179
as the skin you once touched

270
00:15:49,180 --> 00:15:52,419
is slowly bitten away, piece by piece,

271
00:15:52,420 --> 00:15:56,060
while all you can do is scream
in helpless agony.

272
00:16:36,837 --> 00:16:38,546
♪Too bad the rain will stop♪

273
00:16:38,547 --> 00:16:41,396
♪The wind will fade,
tomorrow will clear♪

274
00:16:41,397 --> 00:16:44,136
♪I'd rather this night never end♪

275
00:16:44,137 --> 00:16:45,766
♪Let the long shadows♪

276
00:16:45,767 --> 00:16:51,367
♪whisper what's in your heart♪

277
00:16:51,417 --> 00:16:53,016
♪If in a dream♪

278
00:16:53,017 --> 00:16:55,776
♪I can hear your voice♪

279
00:16:55,777 --> 00:16:58,626
♪Then let it be our meeting♪

280
00:16:58,627 --> 00:17:01,226
♪Let it be us♪

281
00:17:01,227 --> 00:17:06,016
♪drawing endlessly close♪

282
00:17:06,017 --> 00:17:07,776
♪Too bad the rain will stop♪

283
00:17:07,777 --> 00:17:10,427
♪The wind will fade,
tomorrow will clear♪

284
00:17:10,647 --> 00:17:13,366
♪I can't even hold you properly♪

285
00:17:13,367 --> 00:17:15,016
♪Not even in time♪

286
